(820, 1, '2012-01-22 23:56:26', '2012-01-22 23:56:26', '<a name="top"></a>\nDownload <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/pub?key=0AhfikJpJj0uVdGtmNnpjQV9Gb05rN2k5Z01LY1dFcnc&amp;single=true&amp;gid=0&amp;output=html">Spring/Summer Schedule</a>\n\n<a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/#schedule" target="_blank">Visit our LIVE Schedule</a>\n<p style="text-align: left"><span style="text-align: right">Looking for tap &amp; Irish classes? Visit our neighbors <a title="Boston Percussive Dance" href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/boston-percussive-dance/" target="_blank">Boston Percussive Dance</a></span></p>\n\n\n[caption id="attachment_890" align="alignright" width="300" caption="Photo by Liza Voll Photography"]<img class="size-medium wp-image-890 " src="http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/files/2012/01/LizaVollPhotography-1870-300x199.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="199" />[/caption]\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a title="Teachers &amp; Artists in Residence" href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/?page_id=174" target="_blank">Teacher Bios click here.</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="#modern"><strong>MODERN</strong></a>\n\n<a href="#ballet"><strong>BALLET</strong></a>\n\n<a href="#improv"><strong>MOVEMENT TRAINING &amp; IMPROVISATION</strong></a>\n\n<a href="#jazz"><strong>JAZZ &amp; HIP HOP</strong></a>\n\n<a href="#childrens"><strong>CHILDREN’S DANCE</strong></a>\n\n<a href="#latin"><strong>LATIN DANCE</strong></a>\n\n<a href="#traditional"><strong>TRADITIONAL  DANCE/ECLECTIC</strong></a>\n\nBalkan Dance\n\nMiddle Eastern/BellyDance\n\nBollywood\n\nHawaiian\n\n<a href="#tap"><strong>TAP, IRISH DANCE, FLAMENCO</strong></a>\n\n<strong>\n</strong>\n\n<strong> </strong>\n\n<strong>**For Schedule Changes and Cancellations, please visit our  <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/#livesched" target="_blank">(LIVE SCHEDULE)</a></strong>, dates below may not reflect changes.**\n<a id="modern" name="modern"></a><a id="advbegmod" name="advbegmod"></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong> </strong>\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>MODERN</strong></span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Advanced Beginning Modern <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#jody" target="_blank">(Jody Weber)</a></strong>\n\nThis class is for adult dancers with some experience and a basic understanding of dance vocabulary. It’s a great place to start if you are coming back to dance.  The class explores a full understanding of the spine, expanded vocabulary, alignment, and musicality through full bodied phrases. Friendly atmosphere!\n\nMondays 7:30-9:00pm July 9th-Aug 13th\n\n$100 pre-register or $17 for drop-ins -  Drop-ins $17\n<a id="contemp" name="contemp"></a>\nRegistration available at: http://www.weberdance.com/classes-and-workshops.html\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong> Open Level Contemporary <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#chien" target="_blank">(Chien Hwe)</a></strong>\nMondays 5:45-7:15pm\n$15 drop in, $120 pre-registration for the entire summer. (pre-registration required by June 30th)\n\n1,000 Virtues Contemporary Dance SUMMER SERIES\n\nTECHNIQUE - ballet, horton, yoga, choreography.  Build strength and coordination to your core, breath through movement.  $15 for drop-in, $60 for July Series\n\nAUGUST (4 weeks) - IMPROV - meditation, visualization, improvisation, partnering and choreography.  Build trust and fluidity with your own body.  $15 for drop-in, $45 for August Series.\n\nPre-register for July, August or ENTIRE summer series by emailing chienhwe@gmail.com before June 30th. <span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>If you pay for the entire Summer Series on or before June 30th, the price is $100.</strong></span>  Non-refundable payment of half required on or before the first day of the series.  A minimum of 6 people are required for this class to continue.   <a href="http://www.1000virtues.com">www.1000virtues.com</a>\n\n<a id="modrebecca" name="modrebecca"></a>\n\n<strong>Intermediate/Advanced Modern <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#rebecca" target="_blank">(Rebecca Rice)</a></strong>\n\nClasses focus on developing technical, theatrical performers and build strong, musical and organic movers. Influences range from Bill Evans/ Limon-based modern, Gerri Houlihan, Laban Effort Shape &amp; various Pilates and Evan’s-based  floor work. Included will be Modern floor barre, standing center barre, full, contemporary movement &amp; new choreographic ideas. Attention to working with challenging rhythms in order to build strong musicality will be stressed as well as attention to movement that builds virtuosity of technique and creative self-expression. To register or for info email <a href="mailto:riceflan@gmail.com" target="_blank">riceflan@gmail.com</a>.\n<a id="intmodjody" name="intmodjody"></a>\nTuesdays 5:45-7:15pm -  June 5- July 10 - Drop-ins $18\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Intermediate Modern Technique <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#jody" target="_blank">(Jody Weber)</a></strong>\n\nIntermediate modern is a challenging class for dancers with experience. The class focuses on a deep understanding of the body and incorporates ideas from Limon, Cunningham and Graham techniques. Dancers will move through a warm-up that builds strength and clarifies alignment followed by extended phrases which are rhythmically and physically challenging.  The class also focuses on performance quality, focus and presence. Generous atmosphere and live music.\n\nWednesdays  -  $100 Pre-registration -  Drop-ins $17 <strong> ** Substitute Cheri Opperman until Aug 9th** (see below)</strong>\n\nRegistration available at: <a href="http://www.weberdance.com/classes-and-workshops.html" target="_blank">http://www.weberdance.com/classes-and-workshops.html</a>\n\n*WD Community Performance Project 7:30-8:30 – Pre-Registration Required <strong>**Resumes in Aug**</strong>\n\nThis is an open process to learn original choreography performed throughout the year. All participants must register for technique class, but there is no additional cost for the performance group. Interested<a id="intromod" name="intromod"></a> students should email Jody at <a href="mailto:weberdance@rcn.com" target="_blank">weberdance@rcn.com</a>\n\n***Special Summer Classes***\n\n<strong>Intermediate/Advanced Modern Technique with Cheri Opperman</strong>\n\nWednesday 6-7:30pm studio 1 -- Beginning June 6th - Aug 1st\nLive musical accompaniment provided by Jerr Bussiere\nSingle class/drop in $17 --- Email Cheri Opperman for more info at cheriop@ren.com\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Intro to Modern <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#sarahm" target="_blank">(Sarah Mae Gibbons)</a></strong>\n\nIntro to modern dance is a class that looks at modern dance through the methods of technique, improvisation and composition. Each class includes warm-up, floor work and across the floor sequences. In this way we will explore weight, suspension, release, strength, flexibility and creativity.  Exercises and combinations encourage comfort and understanding of personal movement vocabulary.\n\nNo prior experience necessary. Email: <a href="mailto:smgibbons.72@gmail.com" target="_blank">smgibbons.72@gmail.com</a> for information\n<a id="modnicole" name="modnicole"></a>\nThursdays 6:30-7:30 -<strong> Classes to resume in Aug</strong> -  $12 drop-in\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Intermediate/Advanced Modern <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#nicole" target="_blank">(Nicole Pierce)</a></strong>\n\nThis is a fast-moving class for experienced dancers. We will explore technical problems through a mix of classical &amp; idiosyncratic movement vocabularies. Pierce is known for long phrases of challenging, inventive, textural movement,  as well as keen musicality and rhythm. While she enjoys pushing technique and mental acuity, she nurtures an atmosphere of levity and acceptance in order to encourage creative interpretation and the development of one''s own voice. Warm-up is thorough and relevant to the class work.  Live guitar, voice &amp; drums by Jerry Bussiere Pierce and accompanist Jerry Bussiere have worked together for over 15 years and enjoy working in unusual rhythms at many tempos. Never the same class twice! Lots of new material every week.\n<a id="luminarium" name="luminarium"></a>\nThursdays 5:45-7:15pm – Ongoing - $17/drop-ins\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Luminarium Open Class</strong> <strong><a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#merli" target="_blank">(Merli V. Guerra &amp; Kimberleigh Holman)</a></strong>\n\nDesigned for experienced dancers at the intermediate/advanced level, Luminarium''s Open Company Class provides a welcoming, yet challenging atmosphere for local students and performers. Come dance alongside Luminarium Company Members while learning the two unique styles of Artistic Directors Merli V. Guerra and Kimberleigh A. Holman in a fun environment. There are 12 classes in the Spring Session, alternating bi-weekly between Guerra''s contemporary movement with a hint of Classical Indian influence, and Holman''s "whimsically physical" modern technique. If you''re looking to diversify your technique, keep your brain and body active, or simply learn more about the company, join us for this elastically-charged class. Questions? Email <a href="mailto:info@luminariumdance.org" target="_blank">info@luminariumdance.org</a>\n\nPrice: $10 drop in, $85/10-class card\n<a id="modmarcus" name="modmarcus"></a>\n7:30pm-8:45pm New Session begins July 12\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong> ** see alternate summer schedule** Intermediate/Advanced Modern <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#marcus" target="_blank">(Marcus Schulkind)</a></strong>\n\nUsing the concepts of contract/release, drop/flow,  weightedness, and aerial precision, this class consists of floorwork, center work, a barre, and combinations that use the founding principles of modern dance and evolve them to the present. Live music!\n\nFridays  9:30-11:30am – Ongoing - $17.50/drop-in\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Moving Target Series (<a href="http://movingtargetboston.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">Various Guest Teachers</a>)</strong>\n\nAll moving target classes integrate improvisation with technique(s) rooted in pomo/release technique, somatic forms, martial arts, more. Class series is curated by Lauren Simpson and Annie Kloppenberg. We bring fabulous OOT (out-of-town) teachers and EQUALLY FABULOUS in-town teachers. MT is also about developing community around physical inquiry as a shared experience with class givers and class takers. Please feel free to contact us with questions. <a href="http://movingtargetboston.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">http://movingtargetboston.wordpress.com/</a>\n\nSaturdays 2:00 - 4:00pm – Ongoing - 5 class card or drop-in. Check website for rates.\n\n<a href="#top">back to top</a>\n\n<a id="ballet" name="ballet"></a><a id="marley" name="marley"></a>\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>BALLET</strong></span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong> ** see alternate summer schedule ** Back to the Marley <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#marcus" target="_blank">(Marcus Schulkind)</a></strong>\n\nA connective tissue placement class utilizing Marcus'' 47 years of movement principles, to align and revitalize the fascia and muscles, utilizing meridian energies and muscular skeletal exercises. All levels.\n\nFridays 8:30-9:30am, Saturday &amp; Sunday 10-11am – Ongoing - $15/drop-in\n<a id="balletmarcus" name="balletmarcus"></a>\n<strong>** see alternate summer schedule** Intermediate/Advanced Ballet <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#marcus" target="_blank">(Marcus Schulkind)</a></strong>\n\nFirst hour: traditional ballet barre stressing placement, line, musicality, and groundedness. Second hour: adagio, turning phrases, petite allegro,  And grand allegro. Live music.\n<a id="balletdean" name="balletdean"></a>\nSaturdays &amp; Sundays 11am-1pm – Ongoing - $12/barre $17.50/full class\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Intermediate/Advanced Ballet <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#dean" target="_blank">(Dean Vollick)</a></strong>\n\nAn intermediate/advanced ballet class comprised of barre, centre and traveling exercises that are designed to fine tune balance, coordination, and musicality. A challenging class to help any dancer stay in shape, or to prepare for a day of rehearsals. Live music!\n<a id="improv" name="improv"></a>\nWednesdays 10-11:30am –<strong> Resumes Aug 15th</strong> - $15/drop-in\n<a id="improvolivier" name="improvolivier"></a>\n<a href="#top">back to top</a>\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>MOVEMENT TRAINING &amp; IMPROVISATION</strong></span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Contact Improvisation: Skills for Dancers &amp; Choreographers <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#olivier" target="_blank">(Olivier Besson)</a> NEW!</strong>\n\nThis class is for dancers and choreographers who want to use contact improvisation to develop and enhance their understanding of partnering. Contact Improvisation (CI) started as a means to explore the physical forces imposed on the body by gravity and by the physics of momentum. In this class, we will work with sensations and images to generate patterns of movement through direct action (roll, slide, spiral, rise, fall, counterbalance, support, lift, loft and catch). Areas of exploration will include establishing a relationship to ground, developing an internal sense of movement, following points of contact, expanding spatial awareness and integrating leading and following skills in partnering.\n\nTuesdays 7:30-9PM / May15th through June 19th\n\nSix week session/$75\n<a id="improvliz" name="improvliz"></a>\nDrop in/$15\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Movement Improvisation <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#liz" target="_blank">(Liz Roncka)</a>NEW!</strong>\n\nThis class is open to everyone and anyone interested in increasing his or her creativity, awareness, sensitivity and responsivity to the environment. We approach improvisation as a performance form and cultivate our skills in movement invention and instant composition. However, we remain conscious that all of life is an improvisation. The skills we build in class are applicable to all parts of our lives... inside and outside of the studio. Come explore.\n\nThursdays 7:30-9:00pm - Ongoing - $15/drop-in\n<a id="jazz" name="jazz"></a><a id="modjazz" name="modjazz"></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong> </strong>\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>JAZZ &amp; HIP HOP</strong></span>\n\n<strong>\n</strong>\n\n<strong>Int. Modern/Jazz <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#andy" target="_blank">(Andy Taylor-Blenis)</a></strong>\n\nIntermediate modern jazz focuses on body alignment, core strength-building and an expanding dance vocabulary using a variety of modern and Jazz styles and techniques.\n<a id="hiphop" name="hiphop"></a>\nWednesdays 7:30-9:30pm – Ongoing - $15/drop-in\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Hip Hop <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#tarikh" target="_blank">(Tarikh Campbell)</a></strong>\n\nPrior dance experience is encouraged, but not required!  This advanced hip hop class focuses on executing movements with precision, directing power to different parts of the body, and channeling the attitude of the music.  Main styles are swagger, romance, and isolation.  Be ready to sweat!\n\nSaturdays 4:00-5:00pm – Ongoing - $5/drop-in; email <a href="mailto:tcamp09@alum.mit.edu" target="_blank">tcamp09@alum.mit.edu</a>\n\n<a href="#top">back to top</a><a id="childrens" name="childrens"></a>\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>CHILDREN’S DANCE</strong></span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Creative Dance <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#katie" target="_blank">(Katie Dealy)</a></strong>\n\nChildren''s classes combine strong technical skills with a nurturing creative environment. Classes engage imagination, employ props, storytelling and elementary technique. Register (617)-323-6376.\n\nWednesdays 2:45-3:45pm, Ages 2-4 – Pre-registration Required, please call. Classes End from June 27th- Aug 8th\n\nTuesday 11:45- 12.15 Begins June 26th-Augest 7th (no class July 3rd) - Pre-registration Required, please call.\n<a id="groovy" name="groovy"></a>\n<strong>Music Together (<a href="http://groovybabymusic.com/" target="_blank">Groovy Baby Music</a>)</strong>\n\nMusic &amp; movement classes for children newborn to age 5 and their parents. Sing, dance, play instruments, &amp; learn about your child''s music development.  Our teachers are experienced educators and professional musicians. CDs, Songbook, and Parent Guide included.\n\nWednesdays 9-12am – July 11th- Aug 15th Pre-registration Required - Register at <a href="http://groovybabymusic.com" target="_blank">groovybabymusic.com</a>\n\n<strong>Rhythm Kids</strong> (Groovy Baby Music)\n\nDrum like an animal (ages 3-5)\n\nThursdays May 3rd-June 28th 9:00am, 10:00am - Register at <a href="http://www.rhythmkids.com/">http://www.rhythmkids.com</a>\n\n<a href="#top">back to top</a>\n<a id="salsa" name="salsa"></a>\n<a id="latin" name="latin"></a>\n\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>LATIN DANCE</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Salsa: Beginning/Intermediate <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#matei" target="_blank">(Matei Livianu)</a></strong>\n\nMaster the fundamentals of Salsa while learning combinations and footwork in a fun environment. Focus on the basic steps and technique including essential rhythm, leading/following, isolation, and more. Adv.Beginning &amp; Intermediate Series:\n\nPreregistration Required Email <a href="mailto:salsamatei@gmail.com" target="_blank">info@salsamatei.com</a> for info.\n\nAdvanced Beginner Salsa (Level 2) - 7:30-8:30pm $14/drop in\nJune 12th- July 10th\n\nIntermediate Salsa (Level 3) - 8:30-9:30pm $14/drop in\nJune 12t-July 10th\n\n<strong>**summer break until Sept**</strong>\n<a id="traditional" name="traditional"></a>\n<a id="balkan" name="balkan"></a>\n<span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>TRADITIONAL DANCE/ECLECTIC</strong></span>\n\n<strong>Caribbean Movement (All levels)</strong>\n\nThis class is open to those interested in exploring Caribbean beats and creative movement that celebrates the spirit. Experience a fusion of Reggaeton, Salsa, Bachata, Mergengue and Bellydance to create awareness in the body while opening the hips and exploring weight and movement to a dynamic soundtrack from Puerto Rico and neighboring islands. This class consists of a warm-up, isolations, and encourages exploration in movement while incorporating technical aspects such as popping and hip-shakes.\n\nNo prior experience necessary. Email: <a href="mailto:cassandra.fradera@gmail.com">cassandra.fradera@gmail.com</a> with any question you may have.\n\nFridays 6:30-7:30 - Drop/in: $10.00\n\nClass runs from July 6<sup>th</sup> to August 24<sup>th</sup>\n<strong>Cap0eira (Mestre Chuvisco)</strong>\n\nCapoeira is an Afro-Brazilian art form that combines elments of dance, martial arts, music and acrobatics into a fluid game between two players. Training capoeira helps develop stamina, flexibility, strength and self-awareness.\n\nMestre Chuvisco has been teaching capoeira in and around Boston for over 10 years and has been training for over 30. All ages and levels of experience are welcome.Come visit us and learn more about this amazing art form.\n\nTuesday 7:30-8:30 July 3rd- Aug 28th Contact  <a href="mailto:jason_ri@alum.colby.edu">jason_ri@alum.colby.edu</a> for information.\n\n<strong>Balkan Dance <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#peter" target="_blank">(Peter Petrov)</a></strong>\n\nStudents will learn traditional dances from the Balkans. Lovely and energetic dances in ancient and modern styles. All levels welcome. For info call (617) 840-2362\n<a id="belly" name="belly"></a>\nMondays 6:30 – 9pm – Ongoing\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Middle Eastern Dance &amp; BellyDance <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#najmat" target="_blank">(Najmat)</a></strong>\n\nTuesdays 6-7:30pm –Pre-Registration Required - Call (617) 775-9898 to register\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Hawaiian Dance <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/teachers-artists-in-residence/#marta" target="_blank">(Marta Moussa)</a></strong>\n\nThis is an intermediate level class in which students work on hula technique &amp; repertoire. A variety of traditional and ''auana(modern) hulas are taught.  For information on beginner classes email <a href="mailto:polynesiandancearts@yahoo.com" target="_blank">polynesiandancearts@yahoo.com</a>.\n\nWednesdays  6-7:30pm - Pre-registration Required – Call (781)721-1080 to register.\n\n<a href="#top">back to top</a>\n\n<strong>Beginning Hula</strong> (Marta Moussa)\n\nIn this beginner level series , students will learn basic hula movements and terminology, utilizing these movements in learning a beginning level hula.  In keeping with hula''s story telling nature, the meaning of the song will be explained.\nClass attire: capris, shorts, leggings, or pareo(sarong-3 yds cotton fabric or pa''u (traditional hula skirt-nice but not necessary). We will dance in bare feet. NO long pants, long skirts, or baggy outfits.\n\nWednesdays 7:30-8:30pm studio 2  ---- Fee: $72.00 for 6 week series. July 11- Aug 15th\n\nPre-registration is required.  Contact Marta for information to register for the series.\npolynesiandancearts@yahoo.com\n\n<a id="tap" name="tap"></a>\n<strong><span style="text-decoration: underline"><strong>TAP, IRISH DANCE, FLAMENCO</strong></span></strong>\n\nVisit our neighbors<strong> <a title="Boston Percussive Dance" href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/boston-percussive-dance/" target="_blank">Boston Percussive Dance</a>\n</strong>', 'Class Descriptions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'class-descriptions', '', '', '2012-01-22 23:56:26', '2012-01-22 23:56:26', '', 1556, 'http://107.20.220.20/wordpress/?page_id=820', 0, 'page', '', 0),
