(1400, 1, '2012-03-02 03:49:50', '2012-03-02 03:49:50', '&nbsp;\n\nContact: Mariela Cerda                                                                                                          FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE\n\nCell phone: 617-955-7308\n\nemail: <a href="mailto:mariela.cerda@gmail.com" target="_blank">mariela.cerda@gmail.com</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style="text-align: center"><strong>       GREEN STREET STUDIOS 20 YEAR ANNIVERSARY</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center"><strong></strong><strong>           Gala Fundraising</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center"><em>"20 years of work, 20+ types of dance, </em><em>200+ artists, 2,000+ performances, $20,000 to keep this alive"</em></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nGreen Street Studios is celebrating its 20 year anniversary with an unique and unforgettable Gala on Saturday, May 12th, 8pm, at 185 Green St., Cambridge, MA 02139.\n\nAn amazing list of important choreographers and dancers will be performing such as David Dorfman, Sean Curran Dancers, David Parker /The Bang Group, Marcus Schulkind, Lorraine Chapman The Company, Sean Fielder/Boston Tap Company, Nicole Pierce/EgoArt, Inc., Contrapose, Gianni Di Marco &amp; Adriana Suárez, and Josh Hilberman.\n\nIn honor of its 20 years, there will be a special tribute to Green Street Studios founders: Marcus Schulkind, Cheri Opperman, Ruth Birnberg, Paula Josa-Jones and Pam White.  The Gala will conclude with a reception and a party with additional small format performances.\n\nTickets are $100 (Special Guest), $50 (Gala and Reception), and $25 (Gala).\n\nIn conjunction with this historical Gala, an online Fundraiser was launched on March, where people can donate to support Green Street Studios and in this way help one of most important and iconic dance venues on the East Coast.\n\nFor reservations, donations, and additional information see:http://greenstreetstudios.org/performances-events/2012-gala/\n\nFor up dates in the press page see: http://greenstreetstudios.org/about-us/press-page/\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIf you would like more information about this event contact:  Mariela Cerda at 617-955-7308 or <a href="mailto:mariela.cerda@gmail.com" target="_blank">mariela.cerda@gmail.com</a>\n\nIf you would like to schedule an interview with the artists, please contact: Green Street Studios at <a href="617-864-3191">617-864-3191</a> or <a href="mailto:info@greenstreetstudios.org" target="_blank">info@greenstreetstudios.org</a>', 'Press Page', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'press-page', '', '', '2012-03-02 03:49:50', '2012-03-02 03:49:50', '', 47, 'http://greenstreetstudios.org/?page_id=1400', 0, 'page', '', 0);
