(2057, 1, '2012-05-09 04:36:14', '2012-05-09 04:36:14', '<div style="padding-left: 30px">\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">Our 20th Anniversary Gala to be held on Saturday, May 12th is fast approaching! We’d like to take this opportunity to share our excitement in this landmark celebration and the importance of the associated fundraising campaign to Green Street’s continued success.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">For 20 years, Green Street Studios has been a laboratory for dance in the Boston area. Founded originally by five choreographers who needed space for their creative dance work, Green Street has evolved as a dance and movement arts center that is now home to hundreds of dancers who rehearse and study, and over 20 teachers in a range of disciplines.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">What makes Green Street so special is that it provides students of ALL ages and skill levels, and the wider public, the opportunity to experience the beauty and traditions of diverse dance forms in an intimate and friendly creative environment.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 60px">Our Anniversary Gala is a joyous celebration of our:\n<strong>20 years of work</strong>\n<strong> 20+ types of dance</strong>\n<strong> 200+ artists</strong>\n<strong> 2,000+ performances</strong></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">We want Green Street Studios to serve the creative Boston dance community for another 20 years, but we need your help to make this a reality. That’s why we have launched a fundraising campaign to raise $20,000.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">In recent years, our operating costs such as monthly rent have risen substantially while some needed improvements have been deferred. At the same time, we have resisted raising rental fees for teachers, artists, and choreographers in our efforts to continually provide high quality, affordable space. Memberships, donations, and rental income have not kept pace with rising costs, resulting in a funding shortfall.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">The $20,000 will support Green Street''s maintenance and improvements, as well as provide a cushion toward our expected rental increase this summer. We are also developing a more sustainable business model and are looking for new facility users, Green Street sponsors and supporters. Any suggestions you have in this regard would be welcomed.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">Please join us in supporting the<strong> continued success of Green Street Studios</strong>. You can do so by purchasing tickets to the May 12th gala, which promises to be a beautiful and memorable night. If you can''t attend the performance, or even if you can, please consider a donation...$20, $50, or any other amount you can give. There is a simple online donation page, and your gift is tax deductible.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">We are grateful for your support of Green Street Studios and we look forward to celebrating dance with you on May 12th and beyond!</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">Best Wishes,\nGreen Street Studios Board of Directors</p>\n\n</div>', 'Dear Friends and Members of Green Street Studios:', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'dear-friends-and-members-of-green-street-studios', '', '', '2012-05-09 04:36:14', '2012-05-09 04:36:14', '', 1409, 'http://greenstreetstudios.org/?page_id=2057', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(2080, 1, '2012-05-14 18:16:39', '2012-05-14 18:16:39', 'Thank you to everyone who came out to support our 20th Anniversary Gala; a fantastic audience, crew, and group of performers all made for a sensational evening. Many thanks to all our friends who made the evening possible: the fabulous Jayne Murphy and tech crew, GSS Board and staff, Gala Coordinator Mariela Cerda, MC Nicole Pierce, Jimena Bermejo Black, William Parsons, Kieran Jordan &amp; Julia Boynton and all of Boston Percussive Dance, our dedicated volunteers, the GSS founders, and finally, the talented choreographers and performers whose brilliance and generosity made the show shine.', 'Thank You', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', '2080', '', '', '2012-05-14 18:16:39', '2012-05-14 18:16:39', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.org/?p=2080', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2087, 1, '2012-05-24 16:15:20', '2012-05-24 16:15:20', 'Read the review of our 20th Anniversary Gala in the Boston Globe! "Saturday night’s gala performance showcased not just the range but the technical prowess and emotional resonance of that work. The 10 dances by nine choreographers swung in tone from understated wit to thumping drama, lickety-split tapping to lush falls and recovery. Uniting them all were brio and heart." - Thea Singer\n\n<a href="http://b.globe.com/MopYbl" rel="nofollow nofollow" target="_blank">http://b.globe.com/MopYbl</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPLUS! Scroll through the after party photos featured in the Globe! <a href="http://www.boston.com/lifestyle/specials/bill_brett/may2012?pg=11" rel="nofollow nofollow" target="_blank">http://www.boston.com/lifestyle/specials/bill_brett/may2012?pg=11</a>', 'Read our Gala review in the Boston Globe &amp; check out the party photos!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'read-our-gala-review-in-the-boston-globe-check-out-the-party-photos', '', '', '2012-05-24 16:15:20', '2012-05-24 16:15:20', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.org/?p=2087', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2099, 1, '2012-05-27 16:10:11', '2012-05-27 16:10:11', 'View our new <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/pub?key=0AhfikJpJj0uVdGtmNnpjQV9Gb05rN2k5Z01LY1dFcnc&amp;single=true&amp;gid=0&amp;output=html" target="_blank">GSS Schedule Spring and Summer 2012</a>\n\nMay, 2012\n\nDear Students:\n\nAs some of you may know, starting 5/21 Marcus Schulkind will not be teaching due to his recovery from knee surgery. The exact date of his return will be determined, however we anticipate he will be out all of May, June, &amp; July (and possibly some of August). During this time we have a fantastic roster of artists teaching in his place (see details below). We are working hard to bring you a great group of teachers, so please check back for more updates throughout the summer. Please feel free to email us with questions on who is teaching and when at <a href="mailto:info@greenstreetstudios.org">info@greenstreetstudios.org</a>. Thanks!\n\nSincerely,\nGreen Street Studios<strong><strong></strong></strong>\n\n<strong>SUBSTITUTIONS FOR MARCUS’ CLASSES:</strong>\n\nThe weekend of May 25, 26, 27: All Classes with Marcus Schulkind are CANCELED\nFri, June 1: Back to the Marley &amp; Modern CANCELED\nSat, June 2: Olivier Besson Contact Improvisation Workshop 10:30-1pm in place of classes\nSun, June 3: Rosann Ridings starts session: Ballet 11-12:45pm\n(see below)\nFri, June 8: Nicole Pierce starts session: Modern 9:30-11:30am\n(see below)\nSat, June 9: Olivier Besson Contact Improvisation Workshop 10:30-1pm in place of classes\nFriday, June 15: Gyrokinesis with Lisa Pari starts session 8:30-9:30am (see below)\n\n<strong><strong>\nFRIDAYS:\nInt/Adv Modern with Nicole Pierce 9:30-11:30am\n</strong></strong>6 Weeks June 8, 15, 22, 29,  July 6 and 13.\nPay-up-front price of $90.00 ($15/class) or $17 for drop-ins. $10 student rate.<strong><strong></strong></strong>\n\nGyrokenisis with Lisa Pari  8:30-9:30 am\nStarts June 15\nmore info coming soon<strong><strong></strong></strong>\n\n<strong>SATURDAYS:</strong>\n<strong>Back to the Marley 10-11am TBA</strong>\n\n<strong>June 2nd &amp; 9th: Olivier Besson Contact Improvisation Workshop</strong>\n10:30-1pm in place of classes\nJune 2nd / floor work and low flying\nJune 9th / rise, fall and counterbalance\nBoth/$45\nDrop in/$25<strong><strong></strong></strong>\n\nOlivier Besson is an improviser, choreographer and teacher who hails from France and is based in Boston. He has studied contact improvisation with Robin Feld, Nancy Stark Smith, Lisa Nelson and Andrew Harwood. Olivier’s work has been presented in Japan, Russia, France, Taiwan and the US. He is currently teaching improvisation and contact improvisation at The Boston Conservatory and has been on faculty at Canal Danse (Paris), the French National Circus School, Bates Dance Festival, Emerson College and the School of Fine Arts at Boston University.\n<strong><strong>\n</strong></strong>\n\n<strong>July 21 &amp; 28: David Leventhal of the Mark Morris Dance Group. more info coming soon</strong>\n\n<strong>SUNDAYS:</strong>\n<strong>Back to the Marley 10-11am TBA</strong>\n\n<strong>BALLET taught by Rosann Ridings: 11:00-12:45pm</strong>\nStarts June 3rd through July 22nd\n$16 drop-ins\n\nUnder the artistic direction of  E. Virginia Williams, Ms. Ridings became a member of the Boston Ballet Company. She later danced with the Copley Square Ballet and has performed as a guest artist throughout New England. her teaching experience includes: Ballet Theatre of Boston, Classical Ballet of Boston, Dean Junior College and the prestigious Chautaugua Institution in New York. She is a former director of the Cambridge Ballet Center and is currently teaching at the Dance Complex in Cambridge, Mass, and the Lexington School of Ballet, Ballet New England, Donna Coco’s Performance Plus, as well as judging several national dance competitions.<strong><strong></strong></strong>\n\n* We will post more information/classes as we go. Check back often and feel free to email us at <a href="mailto:info@greenstreetstudios.org">info@greenstreetstudios.org</a> for any questions about who is teaching!\n\n* Please visit our <a title="Classes" href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/" target="_blank">LIVE Schedule </a>for an up-to-date listing of Marcus’ classes as well as NEW spring/summer classes including:\n\n<strong><strong>NEW CLASSES!!!</strong></strong>\n\n<strong><strong>Advanced Beginning Modern taught by Jimena Bermejo Black\n</strong></strong>(substitute for Jody Weber)\nMondays 7:30-9:00pm\n4 weeks only: June 4th - June 25th\nMore info coming soon.<strong><strong></strong></strong>\n\n<strong>CONTACT IMPROVISATION:</strong>\n<strong> SKILLS FOR DANCERS AND CHOREOGRAPHERS</strong>\ntaught by Olivier Besson\nTUESDAYS 7:30-9PM / May15th through June 19th\nSix week session/$75\nDrop in/$15\n<strong><strong>\nThis class is for dancers and choreographers who want to use contact improvisation to develop and enhance their understanding of partnering. Contact Improvisation (CI) started as a means to explore the physical forces imposed on the body by gravity and by the physics of momentum. In this class, we will work with sensations and images to generate patterns of movement through direct action (roll, slide, spiral, rise, fall, counterbalance, support, lift, loft and catch). Areas of exploration will include establishing a relationship to ground, developing an internal sense of movement, following points of contact, expanding spatial awareness and integrating leading and following skills in partnering.</strong></strong>\n\n<strong>Intermediate /Advanced modern technique with Cheri Opperman</strong>\nWednesdays 6:00-7:30 pm\n(substitute for Jody Weber)<strong><strong></strong></strong>\n\nBeginning June 6th through August 1st for 8 weeks only\nLive musical accompaniment provided by the incomparable Jerry Bussiere\nClass fees: 8 weeks only- register for the entire session for $120.00\nSingle class/drop in for $17.\nQuestions? Email Cheri at cheriop@rcn.com\n\nCheri Opperman is a Founding Director of Green Street Studios in Cambridge. Cheri has been performing, teaching and choreographing professionally for more than 30 years since receiving her BFA in Dance from the Boston Conservatory. As a member of Susan Rose’s DanceWorks she taught and performed extensively throughout New York and New England and guest taught at the Festival d’Arles, France. At DanceWorks studio she taught elementary through advanced level of modern technique and repertory. As a member of Concert Dance Company she performed in the works of Merce Cunningham, Mark Morris, Kei Ta Kei, Laura Dean, Lucinda Childs, Bebe Miller, Deborah Wolfe, Mark Dendy and many others, and taught company repertory and master classes on tour including the Colorado Dance Festival. Cheri taught at CDC''s School for Contemporary Dance modern and ballet technique, stretch and alignment and company repertory.  Her work has been performed at Green Street Studios, Dance Complex and Emerson Stage. Cheri has been on the dance faculty of Emerson College and recently Harvard University. Cheri is Grants Coordinator for the National Dance Project, a program administered through the New England Foundation for the Arts. Cheri’s teaching style focuses on breath, imagery, dynamic alignment and the pleasure of moving through space. She has a long association with musician Jerry Bussiere, who accompanies classes with live music.\n<strong><strong>\n</strong></strong>\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Movement Improvisation taught by Liz Roncka</strong></p>\n<p dir="ltr">Thursdays 7:30-9:00pm – Ongoing – $15/drop-in</p>\n<p dir="ltr">This class is open to everyone and anyone interested in increasing his or her creativity, awareness, sensitivity and responsivity to the environment. We approach improvisation as a performance form and cultivate our skills in movement invention and instant composition. However, we remain conscious that all of life is an improvisation. The skills we build in class are applicable to all parts of our lives… inside and outside of the studio. Come explore.</p>\n<strong>\n* Please visit our <a title="Classes" href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/" target="_blank">LIVE Schedule</a> for updates!</strong>\n\n* Feel free to email us at <a href="mailto:info@greenstreetstudios.org">info@greenstreetstudios.org</a> for any questions about classes  &amp; teachers!', 'Summer Schedule', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'summer-schedule', '', '', '2012-05-27 16:10:11', '2012-05-27 16:10:11', '', 1556, 'http://greenstreetstudios.org/?page_id=2099', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(2104, 1, '2012-05-27 16:19:12', '2012-05-27 16:19:12', 'Our <a href="http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/files/2012/03/GSS-Schedule-Spring-and-Summer-2012.pdf" target="_blank">Spring/Summer Schedule</a> is here!\n\n*** Please read our important <a title="Summer Schedule" href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/summer-schedule/" target="_blank"> update</a> on Marcus Schulkind''s summer classes and also read about our NEW summer classes including:\n\n<strong>Advanced Beginning Modern taught by Jimena Bermejo Black</strong>\n(substitute for Jody Weber)\nMondays 7:30-9:00pm\n4 weeks only: June 4th - June 25th\n\n<strong>CONTACT IMPROVISATION:</strong>\n<strong>SKILLS FOR DANCERS AND CHOREOGRAPHERS</strong>\n<strong>taught by Olivier Besson</strong>\nTUESDAYS 7:30-9PM / May15th through June 19th\n\n<strong>Intermediate /Advanced modern technique with Cheri Opperman</strong>\nWednesdays 6:00-7:30 pm\n(substitute for Jody Weber)\nBeginning June 6th through August 1st for 8 weeks only\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Movement Improvisation taught by Liz Roncka</strong> on Thursdays 7:30-9:00pm – Ongoing – $15/drop-in</p>', 'Spring/Summer Class Schedule', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'springsummer-class-schedule', '', '', '2012-05-27 16:19:12', '2012-05-27 16:19:12', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.org/?p=2104', 0, 'post', '', 0),
