(2205, 1, '2012-06-11 12:57:13', '2012-06-11 12:57:13', '<p style="text-align: left" align="center"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline">$10,000 worth in prizes give away!!!! $3 each . $10 for 4.  It is really easy:  ask your teacher about the raffle or go to the GSS office, choose a number in a list, write your contact info there, and good luck!!!!</span></strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left" align="center"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline">Winners on June 17<sup>th</sup>,  at 6.30pm , 2012, during the Gala video showing at Green Street Studios.</span></strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Bradford portrait gift card ($5,500 value).</li>\n	<li>Middle East restaurant. Gift card dinner for 2.</li>\n	<li>Green Street Studios t-shirt ($25 value).</li>\n	<li>Green Street Gala poster. (10 separate prints, $10 value each).</li>\n	<li>Liza Voll photography thanks notes package. (5 separate packages, $25 value each)</li>\n	<li>Photowork by Larry Pratt. Title: “Alien Dancers” 7.5x10. ($150 value).</li>\n	<li>Photowork by Larry Pratt. Title: “Forest Fire” 7.5x10. ($150 value).</li>\n	<li>Photowork by Larry Pratt. Title: “Learning to Move” 16x16. ($500 value).</li>\n	<li>Photowork by Larry Pratt. Title: “Contrapose Dance: ‘Ground’ 12x17. ($500 value).</li>\n	<li>Books. Ballets Russes packet. (10 books about Nijinsky, Alicia Markova, Marie Rambert, Ballets-Russes, Diaghilev Ballet, among others).</li>\n	<li>Books. Balanchine Packet. (6 books).</li>\n	<li>Books. American concert dance packet. (9 books about Ruth St. Denis, Ted Shawn, Hanya Holm, among others).</li>\n	<li>Books. American Folk Dance packet.  (4 books about The Round Dance,  The American Square Dance, among others).</li>\n	<li>Books. Tap and Astaire books. (2 books about Fred Astaire).</li>\n	<li>Books. Russian superstars books. (2 books about Nureyev and Baryshnikov).</li>\n	<li>Books. Isadora. (2 books about Isadora Duncan).</li>\n	<li> Books. Misc dance picture books. (3 books about Modern Ballet,  The World Of Ballet and Dance, and Petrushka, Stories of the Ballet).</li>\n	<li>Books. Oversize dance picture books. (4 books about Ballet Portraits, Dance Shoes, Diaghilev and the Ballets Russes,  and The Story of the Dance)</li>\n	<li>MISC ballet books. (3 books about The Nutcracker Ballet, Dance, and Ballet).</li>\n</ol>\n<strong>\n</strong>', 'GREEN STREET STUDIOS 20 YEARS ANNIVERSARY RAFFLE', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'green-street-studios-20-years-anniversary-raffle', '', '', '2012-06-11 12:57:13', '2012-06-11 12:57:13', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.org/?p=2205', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2212, 1, '2012-06-15 16:50:43', '2012-06-15 16:50:43', 'Looking to get more involved and earn free classes? GSS is looking for enthusiastic, reliable work study students for the summer and beyond. Cleaning and office work in exchange for free classes and rehearsal space.\n\nWant to get involved with shows? Ask us about our House Manager Program. Want to get started right away? Come to our video showing this Sunday and help set-up or break-down, we would love to meet you. Email info@greenstreetstudios.org to let us know you want to get in more involved in your Green Street Community!\n\n<a title="Get Involved" href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/get-involved/" target="_blank">Get Involved</a>\n\nThanks to all of our current volunteers! We couldn''t do it without you!', 'GSS seeks Volunteers &amp; Work Study Students! ', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'green-street-seeks-volunteers-and-work-study-students', '', '', '2012-06-15 16:50:43', '2012-06-15 16:50:43', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.org/?p=2212', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2216, 1, '2012-06-15 20:10:58', '2012-06-15 20:10:58', 'Breaking News: Margot Parsons will be teaching Ballet on Saturdays for the summer (substitute for Marcus) starting tomorrow, Saturday June 16th from 11:00-12:45. Full class $16, barre $10. Live pianist. See you there!\n\nVisit our <a title="Classes" href="http://greenstreetstudios.org/classes-2/" target="_blank">LIVE </a>class schedule for summer updates!', 'Margot Parsons teaching Saturdays, Gyrokinesis with Lisa Pari Friday mornings', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'margot-parsons-teaching-saturdays-gyrokinesis-with-lisa-pari-friday-mornings', '', '', '2012-06-15 20:10:58', '2012-06-15 20:10:58', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.org/?p=2216', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2217, 1, '2012-07-08 03:52:00', '2012-07-08 03:52:00', 'Street Address: Green Street Studios 185 Green St Cambridge, MA 02139 USA   Email: General information: info@greenstreetstudios.org Renting information: scheduling@greenstreetstudios.org   Telephone: 1 (617) 864-3191   Keep in Touch!:   Boston Percussive Dance: Boston Percussive Dance is an independent studio founded by tap dancer Julia Boynton and Irish step dancer Kieran Jordan, based in Studio #3 at Green Street.  For information on Boston Percussive classes, performances or festivals, check out their website at: www.bostonpercussivedance.com', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2217', '', '', '2012-07-08 03:52:00', '2012-07-08 03:52:00', '', 47, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2217/', 55, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2218, 1, '2012-07-08 03:52:00', '2012-07-08 03:52:00', 'Green Street Studios is located at 185 Green St., Cambridge, MA in the heart of the Boston dance community in Central Square. The studio is easily accessible by public transportation: we are located 1 block from buses and the Red Line Central Square T stop. Parking is available in the Green Street Garage and at metered parking lots. Our studios are housed in a two story brick building between Pearl St. and Brookline St. Head up the stairs to visit us &amp; our neighbors Boston Percussive Dance!   Directions by Car Parking Directions by Public Transportation Photo Credit: Liza Voll View Larger Map By Car: From Boston Cross the Massachusetts Avenue Bridge into Cambridge. Half a mile from the bridge turn left on Sidney Street (a wide street just before a fire station on the left) and immediately turn right into Green Street. Drive one block to Brookline Street. Cross Brookline Street. Green Street Studio will be the 2nd building on the right. From Mass Turnpike, Brookline Take Cambridge/Allston exit on to River Street Bridge into Cambridge, continue straight on River Street less than half a mile and make a right turn on Franklin Street. Take the 3rd left turn…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2218', '', '', '2012-07-08 03:52:00', '2012-07-08 03:52:00', '', 47, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2218/', 57, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2219, 1, '2012-07-08 03:52:00', '2012-07-08 03:52:00', 'Jimena Bermejo Kieran Jordan Abbie Katz Annie Kloppenberg Toni Matsu David Parker Birute Regine Marcus Schulkind Donna Wabrek       Jimena Bermejo Jimena Bermejo was born in Mexico City holds an MFA in Studio for Interrelated Media from The Massachusetts College of Art and Design and BFA in Dance from The Boston Conservatory. Jimena has performed with Spencer/Colton, Marcus Schulkind, Kate Digby, Ego Art Inc., Kelli Edwards, Lorraine Chapman The Company, Caitlin Corbett Dance Company, Sarah Slifer and as a guest dancer with David Parker and The Bang Group. Along with performing Jimena continues to teach, choreograph and create video/performance pieces. Along with performing Jimena continues to teach, choreograph and create video/performance pieces, Jimena is a dance professor at The College of The Holy Cross and Suffolk University.   Abbie H. Katz Abbie H. Katz was Associate Producer for the Boston Early Music Festival from 2002-07; previous to that she was General Manager of The Market Theater in Cambridge. Ms. Katz was also Associate Producer for the Festival of Arts &amp; Ideas in New Haven and General Manager for Anna Deveare Smith’s Institute on the Arts and Civic Dialogue at Harvard University. She toured extensively throughout the US, Europe…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2219', '', '', '2012-07-08 03:52:00', '2012-07-08 03:52:00', '', 47, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2219/', 59, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2220, 1, '2012-07-08 03:52:00', '2012-07-08 03:52:00', 'Director of Operations Kathryn Dunkel Scheduling Coordinator Sarah Mae Gibbons Treasurer Donna Wabrek Billing Coordinator Toni Matsu Technical Director Erik Fox **Website photos by Liza Voll     Kathryn Dunkel Kathryn Dunkel earned her BA in Dance from Hamilton College with a Minor in Anthropology and is a graduate of the Trinity/La Mama Performance Art program out of New York City. Katie currently dances for Ego Art, Inc. and Falling Flight Project, and has had the pleasure of performing work by choreographers and companies including: Audra Carabetta, Lorraine Chapman, Contrapose Dance, Meghan McLyman, Mariah Steele, Danny Swain Dance Company, and WeberDance. An alumna of the Shared Choreographers Concert (2007) at The Dance Complex &amp; the Emerging Artists Program (2009) at Green Street Studios, Katie has presented her own choreography in Cambridge, MA and New York City. She has taught dance at schools in New York, Vermont, Connecticut, and Massachusetts, and was the Director of Dance at Burr &amp; Burton Academy in Manchester, VT. Most recently, Katie has taught in the Boston area at Wilmington Dance Academy and Green Street Studios and currently teaches dance at Dancers Workshop in Sudbury and Ballet Arts Center of Winchester. Katie also holds her 200-hour…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2220', '', '', '2012-07-08 03:52:00', '2012-07-08 03:52:00', '', 47, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2220/', 61, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
