(2223, 1, '2012-07-08 03:52:01', '2012-07-08 03:52:01', 'Resident Artists Green Street Studios is home to some of Boston’s most engaging and experienced movement artists. Our founding and long time artistic residents engage students on many levels, offering work in classical and innovative movement approaches to contemporary dance. Cheri Opperman is a Founding Director of Green Street Studios in Cambridge where she currently teaches intermediate modern technique. Cheri has been performing, teaching and choreographing professionally for more than 20 years since receiving her BFA in Dance from the Boston Conservatory. As a member of Susan Rose’s DanceWorks she taught and performed extensively throughout New York and New England and guest taught at the Festival d’Arles, France.At DanceWorks studio she taught elementary through advanced level of modern technique and repertory. As a member of Concert Dance Company she performed in the works of Merce Cunningham, Mark Morris, Kei Ta Kei, Laura Dean, Lucinda Childs, Bebe Miller, Deborah Wolfe, Mark Dendy and many others, and taught company repertory and master classes on tour including the Colorado Dance Festival. Cheri taught at CDC’s School for Contemporary Dance modern and ballet technique, stretch and alignment and company repertory. Her work has been performed at Green Street Studios, The Dance Complex and Emerson…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2223', '', '', '2012-07-08 03:52:01', '2012-07-08 03:52:01', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2223/', 9, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2224, 1, '2012-07-08 03:52:01', '2012-07-08 03:52:01', 'Green Street Studios has the following rooms available for your use: Studio #1 Black fully sprung floor with full length mirrors along one wall and a skylight. 2,500 square feet, ( 40 X 60 ). This studio also functions as a performance space, Studio #2 Black fully sprung floor with full length mirrors along one wall and a skylight. 1,500 square foot, ( 35 X 40 ) General Our facilities also include a dressing room and three bathrooms. If you are a dancer/teacher and are interested in renting space in our studios for rehearsing, teaching classes or workshops, or performing, please email all requests to scheduling@greenstreetstudios.org or leave a voicemail in the Space Rental Requests mailbox, only. We will do our best to respond to all requests within 36-48 hours. If you would like your class, workshop, or performance listed on our web site, please e-mail us with all available information. Please be specific about the date, time, and description of the event for the best turnout. PLEASE NOTE: because of the marley flooring, NO STREET SHOES OR HIGH HEELS are allowed in the studios. For more information, please visit our Rental Information page.', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2224', '', '', '2012-07-08 03:52:01', '2012-07-08 03:52:01', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2224/', 14, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
