(2316, 1, '2012-07-08 04:06:55', '2012-07-08 04:06:55', 'Green Street Studios thrives upon the help and support of our volunteers. There are many ways to get involved in your local dance community through GSS. Please contact us at 617-864-3191 if you are interested in volunteering, and be sure to check out our site to see what opportunities are available. Green Street Studios seeks: Events Coordinator Volunteer Coordinator For more information or to apply for any of these positions, please email a cover letter, a resume, and at least 1 reference to info@greenstreetstudios.org or mail materials by July 1st to: Green Street Street Studios 185 Green Street Cambridge, MA 02139   Events Coordinator Qualifications: Candidates must demonstrate a genuine interest in Production/Stage Management in a non-profit arts environment. Must be self-motivated, responsible, efficient at multitasking, punctual, responsive, and have excellent customer service skills. Must be organized and efficient with Microsoft Word, Excel and PayPal. Experience with Production/Stage Management is preferred. Responsibilities include: Communicating with the renters and the Technical Director Communicating with the GSS staff/scheduling coordinator Recruiting volunteers for events (this includes: ushers, cleaners, box office, tech, set up/break down) Creating and distributing contracts Coordinating other events including but not limited to informal showings, master class, workshops. Availability for…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2316', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:06:55', '2012-07-08 04:06:55', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2316/', 18, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2317, 1, '2012-07-08 04:06:56', '2012-07-08 04:06:56', 'Yes! I want to be a Member! Green Street Studios depends on the generosity of its community. If you would like to support our work, please stop by the studio and pick up a membership form (located on the bulletin board at the top of the stairs just outside of Studio 1), download a pdf version, or call the office at 617-864-3191. Member Benefits Include: A bimonthly email newsletter about Green Street plans Advance notice of all special Green Street events A members’ discount at all GSS-produced performances A members’ reception to meet each other, the GSS staff and GSS artists For the artist membership fee, you will receive all of the above, in addition to discounted rehearsal space Monday-Friday at the Studios, and a one-time use of the Studios’ mailing list.  ', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2317', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:06:56', '2012-07-08 04:06:56', '', 34, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2317/', 19, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2318, 1, '2012-07-08 04:06:56', '2012-07-08 04:06:56', 'As a center for developing emerging dance and movement artists, GSS will provide an environment where they can experiment, take artistic risks, perform and grow. GSS will collaborate with the Boston dance community and will bring artists, dancers and Boston’s audiences together to share the best and most challenging ideas, practices and practitioners by providing master classes and workshops with guest artists, offering artist residencies, and presenting performances of current and evolving trends. Check out Green Street’s Emerging Artists Program! “Echoes” Emerging Artists Performance July 8 &amp; 9, 2011 8pm Green Street Studios', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2318', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:06:56', '2012-07-08 04:06:56', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2318/', 20, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
