(2344, 1, '2012-07-08 04:07:03', '2012-07-08 04:07:03', 'Resident Artists Green Street Studios is home to some of Boston’s most engaging and experienced movement artists. Our founding and long time artistic residents engage students on many levels, offering work in classical and innovative movement approaches to contemporary dance. Cheri Opperman is a Founding Director of Green Street Studios in Cambridge where she currently teaches intermediate modern technique. Cheri has been performing, teaching and choreographing professionally for more than 20 years since receiving her BFA in Dance from the Boston Conservatory. As a member of Susan Rose’s DanceWorks she taught and performed extensively throughout New York and New England and guest taught at the Festival d’Arles, France.At DanceWorks studio she taught elementary through advanced level of modern technique and repertory. As a member of Concert Dance Company she performed in the works of Merce Cunningham, Mark Morris, Kei Ta Kei, Laura Dean, Lucinda Childs, Bebe Miller, Deborah Wolfe, Mark Dendy and many others, and taught company repertory and master classes on tour including the Colorado Dance Festival. Cheri taught at CDC’s School for Contemporary Dance modern and ballet technique, stretch and alignment and company repertory. Her work has been performed at Green Street Studios, The Dance Complex and Emerson…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2344', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:07:03', '2012-07-08 04:07:03', '', 1556, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2344/', 11, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2345, 1, '2012-07-08 04:07:03', '2012-07-08 04:07:03', 'Green Street Studios has the following rooms available for your use: Studio #1 Black fully sprung floor with full length mirrors along one wall and a skylight. 2,500 square feet, ( 40 X 60 ). This studio also functions as a performance space, Studio #2 Black fully sprung floor with full length mirrors along one wall and a skylight. 1,500 square foot, ( 35 X 40 ) General Our facilities also include a dressing room and three bathrooms. If you are a dancer/teacher and are interested in renting space in our studios for rehearsing, teaching classes or workshops, or performing, please email all requests to scheduling@greenstreetstudios.org or leave a voicemail in the Space Rental Requests mailbox, only. We will do our best to respond to all requests within 36-48 hours. If you would like your class, workshop, or performance listed on our web site, please e-mail us with all available information. Please be specific about the date, time, and description of the event for the best turnout. PLEASE NOTE: because of the marley flooring, NO STREET SHOES OR HIGH HEELS are allowed in the studios. For more information, please visit our Rental Information page.', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2345', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:07:03', '2012-07-08 04:07:03', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2345/', 12, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2346, 1, '2012-07-08 04:07:03', '2012-07-08 04:07:03', 'Rehearsals Studio #1 – $15.00/hour, Studio #2 – $12.50/hour Artist Members receive discounted Rehearsal Rates Studio 1 – $9.50/hour Studio 2 – $8.50/hour Monday-Friday 9am-5pm CANCELLATION POLICY : One Week Classes/Workshops Studio 1 – $36.50/hour Studio 2 – $32.50/hour Concerts &amp; Performances Two Nights (Friday/Saturday): $1200 Includes: Use of house lighting and sound system Reservations Service Dress Rehearsal Use of our House Technical Director This fee does not include the cost of a Fire Detail from the city of Cambridge, which is required for more than 40 guests.   One Night (Friday or Saturday): $825 Includes: Use of house lighting and sound system Reservations Service Dress Rehearsal Use of our House Technical DirectorFire Detail Informal Showings : $200/night Additional Tech Time: $10/hour Extra Mailing List Use (Green Street Studios Events Only) $50 GSS Members (Once per year) through the mailhouse $75 through the mailhouse $150 On labels CONCERT CANCELLATION POLICY: One Month—initial 25% deposit upon signing contract is non-refundable. back to top', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2346', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:07:03', '2012-07-08 04:07:03', '', 27, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2346/', 13, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2347, 1, '2012-07-08 04:07:04', '2012-07-08 04:07:04', 'Green Street Studios thrives upon the help and support of our volunteers. There are many ways to get involved in your local dance community through GSS. Please contact us at 617-864-3191 if you are interested in volunteering, and be sure to check out our site to see what opportunities are available. Green Street Studios seeks: Events Coordinator Volunteer Coordinator For more information or to apply for any of these positions, please email a cover letter, a resume, and at least 1 reference to info@greenstreetstudios.org or mail materials by July 1st to: Green Street Street Studios 185 Green Street Cambridge, MA 02139   Events Coordinator Qualifications: Candidates must demonstrate a genuine interest in Production/Stage Management in a non-profit arts environment. Must be self-motivated, responsible, efficient at multitasking, punctual, responsive, and have excellent customer service skills. Must be organized and efficient with Microsoft Word, Excel and PayPal. Experience with Production/Stage Management is preferred. Responsibilities include: Communicating with the renters and the Technical Director Communicating with the GSS staff/scheduling coordinator Recruiting volunteers for events (this includes: ushers, cleaners, box office, tech, set up/break down) Creating and distributing contracts Coordinating other events including but not limited to informal showings, master class, workshops. Availability for…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2347', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:07:04', '2012-07-08 04:07:04', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2347/', 16, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2348, 1, '2012-07-08 04:07:04', '2012-07-08 04:07:04', 'Yes! I want to be a Member! Green Street Studios depends on the generosity of its community. If you would like to support our work, please stop by the studio and pick up a membership form (located on the bulletin board at the top of the stairs just outside of Studio 1), download a pdf version, or call the office at 617-864-3191. Member Benefits Include: A bimonthly email newsletter about Green Street plans Advance notice of all special Green Street events A members’ discount at all GSS-produced performances A members’ reception to meet each other, the GSS staff and GSS artists For the artist membership fee, you will receive all of the above, in addition to discounted rehearsal space Monday-Friday at the Studios, and a one-time use of the Studios’ mailing list.  ', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2348', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:07:04', '2012-07-08 04:07:04', '', 34, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2348/', 17, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2349, 1, '2012-07-08 04:07:04', '2012-07-08 04:07:04', 'As a center for developing emerging dance and movement artists, GSS will provide an environment where they can experiment, take artistic risks, perform and grow. GSS will collaborate with the Boston dance community and will bring artists, dancers and Boston’s audiences together to share the best and most challenging ideas, practices and practitioners by providing master classes and workshops with guest artists, offering artist residencies, and presenting performances of current and evolving trends. Check out Green Street’s Emerging Artists Program! “Echoes” Emerging Artists Performance July 8 &amp; 9, 2011 8pm Green Street Studios', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2349', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:07:04', '2012-07-08 04:07:04', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2349/', 21, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2350, 1, '2012-07-08 04:07:04', '2012-07-08 04:07:04', 'Emerging Artists for Winter 2011: Jillian Grunnah Jennifer Hardy Nicole Harris Angie Hartley Emerging Artists Mentors: Karen Krolak and Rozann Kraus Emerging Artists Fall 2010: Kathryn Dunkel Kendra Heithoff Angela Conte Wanda Strukus Sara Smith Mentors: Dean Vollick and Kelli Edwards Emerging Artists for Winter 2009: Abrazo Dance – Vyvane Loh, Melissa Alexis, &amp; Heather Azano-Brown Courtney Peix Mariah Steele Marissa Ventre Emerging Artists for Winter/Spring 2008: Jimena Bermejo Kelli Edwards Betsi Graves Gabrielle Orcha Emerging Artists for Winter/Spring 2006: Choreography by Karl Croni Photography by Julian Russell, Metropl Photos Dancers: Karl Cronin and Sarah Heartt Emerging Artist Award Concert, 2006/12/21 “Three Won’t Lock”, Choreography by Hannah Naiman Photography by Julian Russell, Metropl Photos Dancers: Hannah Naiman, Claire Morrison, Katrina Sukola Emerging Artist Award Concert,2006/12/1,2 “Raw Footage”, Choreography by Lindsay Caddle – Linden Tree Dance Company Photography by Julian Russell, Metropol Photos Dancers: Jill Jackson, Erin Pellecchia, Serena Hadsell, Kathryn Lucek, Jessie Boudreau, Lindsay Caddle New Salt From the Stock, Emerging Artist Award Concert, 2006/12/1,2', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2350', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:07:04', '2012-07-08 04:07:04', '', 43, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2350/', 66, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2351, 1, '2012-07-08 04:07:05', '2012-07-08 04:07:05', 'Green Street Studios is a center for movement and dance that enables artists, students, and audiences to explore the boundless potential of physical movement and the expressive capacity of the human body. Through its support of both established and emerging professionals, Green Street Studios provides students of all levels, and the wider public, the opportunity to explore and establish connections of their own to the traditions and commitments of disciplined movement.', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2351', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:07:05', '2012-07-08 04:07:05', '', 0, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2351/', 22, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2352, 1, '2012-07-08 04:07:05', '2012-07-08 04:07:05', 'Green Street Studios is a 501(c)3 non-profit   Mission Green Street Studios is a center for movement and dance that enables artists, students, and audiences to explore the boundless potential of physical movement and the expressive capacity of the human body. Through its support of both established and emerging professionals, Green Street Studios provides students of all levels, and the wider public, the opportunity to explore and establish connections of their own to the traditions and commitments of disciplined movement. Vision Green Street Studios is a dance and movement arts center that serves all ages and skill levels. GSS will develop dance audiences and serve its diverse community by expanding opportunities to experience the magic and wonder of dance and movement. We will be recognized for our artistic integrity, the quality of our dance education and our progressive programming. GSS will strive to identify and fill voids in the dance and movement community that are in harmony with our mission. The best professionals will be working for GSS. They will be experienced, dedicated to continually improving their teaching technique, recognized by the dance and movement community for their work, and committed to fostering and developing the Green Street Studios community.…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2352', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:07:05', '2012-07-08 04:07:05', '', 47, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2352/', 23, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2353, 1, '2012-07-08 04:07:05', '2012-07-08 04:07:05', 'Director of Operations Kathryn Dunkel Scheduling Coordinator Nicole Kedaroe Treasurer Donna Wabrek Billing Coordinator Toni Matsu Technical Director Eric Fox', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2353', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:07:05', '2012-07-08 04:07:05', '', 47, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2353/', 25, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2354, 1, '2012-07-08 04:07:05', '2012-07-08 04:07:05', 'Jimena Bermejo Kieran Jordan Abbie Katz Annie Kloppenberg Toni Matsu David Parker Birute Regine Marcus Schulkind Donna Wabrek Jimena Bermejo Jimena Bermejo was born in Mexico City holds an MFA in Studio for Interrelated Media from The Massachusetts College of Art and Design and BFA in Dance from The Boston Conservatory. Jimena has performed with Spencer/Colton, Marcus Schulkind, Kate Digby, Ego Art Inc., Kelli Edwards, Lorraine Chapman The Company, Caitlin Corbett Dance Company, Sarah Slifer and as a guest dancer with David Parker and The Bang Group. Along with performing Jimena continues to teach, choreograph and create video/performance pieces. Along with performing Jimena continues to teach, choreograph and create video/performance pieces, Jimena is a dance professor at The College of The Holy Cross and Suffolk University. Kieran Jordan Kieran Jordan is a performer, teacher, and choreographer of Irish dance, and co-founder/director of Boston Percussive Dance. With more than 30 years of experience in Irish dance, Kieran’s unique approach marries deep-rooted traditions with contemporary innovations. She has collaborated with many of New England’s finest traditional musicians, and has toured as a solo dancer and presented her choreography throughout North America and Europe. Kieran has been teaching in the Boston area since…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2354', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:07:05', '2012-07-08 04:07:05', '', 47, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2354/', 26, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(2355, 1, '2012-07-08 04:07:06', '2012-07-08 04:07:06', '  Green Street Studios is located at 185 Green St., Cambridge, MA. View Larger Map By Car: From Boston Cross the Massachusetts Avenue Bridge into Cambridge. Half a mile from the bridge turn left on Sidney Street (a wide street just before a fire station on the left) and immediately turn right into Green Street. Drive one block to Brookline Street. Cross Brookline Street. Green Street Studio will be the 2nd building on the right. For parking look for 2 hour meters (free after 6:00 PM and on Sundays) on Brookline Street before crossing it or continue on Green Street to the Municipal parking lot on the left after the stop sign. Meters also available on Massachusetts Avenue (2 and 1 hour meters). From Mass Turnpike, Brookline Take Cambridge/Allston exit on to River Street Bridge into Cambridge, continue straight on River Street less than half a mile and make a right turn on Franklin Street. Take the 3rd left turn onto Brookline Street and the next left onto Green Street. Parking A reasonably priced parking garage is located on Green Street, the next block after Green Street Studios, on the left side of the street. By Public Transportation: To Central…', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '2355', '', '', '2012-07-08 04:07:06', '2012-07-08 04:07:06', '', 47, 'http://greenstreetstudios.smalls.cc/2012/07/08/2355/', 27, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
