ance release that fixes a few important issues that users were having with the 3.8.8 release. The following issues have been addressed in 3.8.8.2: * CSV sales export now puts the item quanity in a separate column from the product title. * Core [...]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Gary Cao";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1584:"<p>The 3.8.8.2 release of WP e-Commerce is now available. This is a maintenance release that fixes a few important issues that users were having with the 3.8.8 release.</p>\n<p>The following issues have been addressed in 3.8.8.2:</p>\n<pre>* CSV sales export now puts the item quanity in a separate column from the\r\n  product title.\r\n* Core checkout fields cannot be restored if they were deleted before upgrading\r\n  to 3.8.8.\r\n* Insecure SSL resources when WordPress is using SSL, or "Force SSL Checkout"\r\n  is enabled.\r\n* Issue with WPML and Variations.\r\n* Shipping &amp; Total Order values are wrong on Sales Log page.\r\n* Terms and Conditions - Checkout page breaks if you read the terms and\r\n  conditions.\r\n* Total shipping value and total price incorrect in transaction results.\r\n* Variation sales prices are inaccurate in Product Specials Widget</pre>\n<p><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">As always before upgrading it is advised to make a full backup of your site</span></strong> (wp-content directory and a Database backup). If you&#8217;re unsure of how to make a backup then we would recommend you use <a href="http://pluginbuddy.com/purchase/backupbuddy/">Backup Buddy</a>.</p>\n<p>Once backed up you can upgrade your WP e-Commerce plugin from within your plugins menu or you can <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-e-commerce/">download the latest version from WordPress</a> and upload it via FTP.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re having any problems or questions about this release or how to upgrade, please don&#8217;t hesitate to let us know via this blog post.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/3-8-8-2-official-release/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"38";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:47:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"Authorize.net – Configuration and settings explained.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:94:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/authorize-net-configuration-and-settings-explained/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:103:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/authorize-net-configuration-and-settings-explained/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sat, 02 Jun 2012 23:48:16 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"WP e-Commerce Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Authorize.net";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"support";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://getshopped.org/?p=270135";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:291:"Authorize.net is by far the most popular Gold Cart Gateway. From time to time a few of you have issues setting it up, or questions about how to use the settings. Please read below for a run down on these with some solutions. As always if any of you have any other questions relating to [...]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Mychelle";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4937:"<p>Authorize.net is by far the most popular <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-plugin/gold-cart-plugin/">Gold Cart Gateway</a>. From time to time a few of you have issues setting it up, or questions about how to use the settings. Please read below for a run down on these with some solutions. As always if any of you have any other questions relating to authorize.net then please leave a comment on this post and a support team member will be able to respond ASAP!</p>\n<h2>Common Problems</h2>\n<p><strong>Incorrect Account information -</strong> You will be surprised how often this is the case. If you are having a problem then please recheck your account details. Then check them again.</p>\n<p><strong>To obtain your API Login ID:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Log into the Merchant Interface at https://secure.authorize.net</li>\n<li>Select Settings under Account in the main menu on the left</li>\n<li>Click API Login ID and Transaction Key in the Security Settings section</li>\n<li>If you have not already obtained an API Login ID and Transaction Key for your account, you will need to enter the secret answer to the secret question you configured at account activation.</li>\n<li>Click Submit.</li>\n<li>The API Login ID for your account is displayed on the API Login ID and Transaction Key page.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>To obtain a Transaction Key:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Log on to the Merchant Interface at https://secure.authorize.net</li>\n<li>Select Settings under Account in the main menu on the left</li>\n<li>Click API Login ID and Transaction Key in the Security Settings section</li>\n<li>Enter the secret answer to the secret question you configured when you activated your user account</li>\n<li>Click Submit</li>\n<li>The Transaction Key for your account is displayed on a confirmation page.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Be sure to record your Transaction Key immediately in a secure manner or copy it immediately to a file in a secure location because it is not always visible in the Merchant Interface like the API Login ID. Once you navigate away from the confirmation page there will be no other way to access the Transaction Key in the Merchant Interface. You would have to generate a new Transaction Key.</p>\n<p><strong>The Account is not Authorized</strong> &#8211; Authorize.net requires that your live production account be authorized by them, If you have just singed up for this account or are having problems please check that it has been authorized by them.</p>\n<p><strong>Using Test Mode for non test accounts</strong> &#8211; Most of you will have live production accounts unless you asked Authorize.net specially for a test account. Only check the &#8220;test mode&#8221; box if you have a test account.</p>\n<h2>Common Questions</h2>\n<p>Trying to setup  authorize.net but befuddled by the settings?</p>\n<p>You can find a very good run down on each setting at the <a href="http://docs.getshopped.org/documentation/authorize-net/">authorize.net documentation page</a>.</p>\n<p>My checkout form has a select box before displaying the credit card forms, I don&#8217;t want to use e checks so how can I remove this option?<br />\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-270143" title="Screen shot 2012-05-28 at 12.21.15 PM" src="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Screen-shot-2012-05-28-at-12.21.15-PM.png" alt="" width="325" height="157" /><br />\nIf you have this problem and are only going to be using the basic integration (don&#8217;t need E-checks, CIM) then the best way to get rid of this selection and just have the credit card form is to use the older Authorize.net 2.0</p>\n<p>I use the original Authorize.net 2.0 gateway and there is a message saying its not going to be supported for much longer, whats this about?<br />\nIf your using the older gateway you will see a warning about the gateway not going to be supported anymore as there is the new version. Don&#8217;t panic this gateway will still work and its not going to just be removed from the Gold Cart! However if this gateway stops working because Authorize.net change their API or code then this gateway will not undergo a rewrite we will only support the newest one past this point.</p>\n<p><strong>It&#8217;s still not working what should I do?</strong><br />\nFor those of you that know how you can debug the response that is returned from authorize.net this will provide you with an error code and an error message. You can then view what they mean over at authorize.net&#8217;s <a href="http://www.authorize.net/support/merchant/Transaction_Response/Response_Reason_Codes_and_Response_Reason_Text.htm">error code library</a></p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re not a developer have followed all the steps above then we would suggest that you use your<a href="http://getshopped.org/resources/premium-support/"> support token</a> to contact premium support the staff there will be able to debug your gateway for you.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:99:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/authorize-net-configuration-and-settings-explained/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"24";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:44:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:25:"WP e-Commerce 3.8.8.2-dev";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:64:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-8-2-dev/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-8-2-dev/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 29 May 2012 20:52:57 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"GetShopped News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"WP e-Commerce Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://getshopped.org/?p=270384";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:333:"Update (Jun 4th, 2012): An additional bug with shipping &#038; total order values in Sales Log page has been fixed in this 3.8.8.2-dev package. The 3.8.8.1 release has addressed all the major issues with 3.8.8. However, there were still a few minor issues that some of the users are still encountering. As a result, we&#8217;re [...]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Gary Cao";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1919:"<p><strong>Update (Jun 4th, 2012):</strong> An additional bug with shipping &#038; total order values in Sales Log page has been fixed in this 3.8.8.2-dev package.</p>\n<p>The 3.8.8.1 release has addressed all the major issues with 3.8.8. However, there were still a few minor issues that some of the users are still encountering. As a result, we&#8217;re releasing another minor release, 3.8.8.2, in a week. The following issues are fixed in this minor release:</p>\n<pre>* Change: CSV sales export now puts the item quanity in a separate column from\r\n  the product title.\r\n* Core checkout fields cannot be restored if they were deleted before upgrading\r\n  to 3.8.8.\r\n* Insecure SSL resources when WordPress is using SSL, or "Force SSL Checkout"\r\n  is enabled.\r\n* Issue with WPML and Variations.\r\n* Terms and Conditions - Checkout page breaks if you read the terms and\r\n  conditions.\r\n* Total shipping value and total price incorrect in transaction results.\r\n* Total shipping value and total price incorrect in Sales Log details page. (Jun 4th, 2012)\r\n* Variation sales prices are inaccurate in Product Specials Widget</pre>\n<p>In order to make it easy for you to test 3.8.8.2 before we release it officially, we made the 3.8.8.2-dev package available and you can <a href="http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.8.8.2-dev.zip">download it from WordPress.org</a>.</p>\n<p>One very important thing though, as the name 3.8.8.2-dev suggests, the purpose of this package is for you to test. It&#8217;s not guaranteed to be stable yet, so please don&#8217;t use this on your live site unless you really know what you&#8217;re doing. This is supposed to be used on your test site only.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s still recommended that you back up your test site before using this package.</p>\n<p>If you discover any new issues introduced by this 3.8.8.2-dev package, please let us know via the comment section below!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-8-2-dev/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"34";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:47:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"Common Gold Cart Questions Answered!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/common-gold-cart-questions-answered/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:88:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/common-gold-cart-questions-answered/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 28 May 2012 23:17:08 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Gold Cart";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"WP e-Commerce Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://getshopped.org/?p=270101";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:350:"&#8220;I have activated my Gold Cart but grid view doesn&#8217;t work it still tells me to purchase the Gold Cart?&#8221; &#8220;I have uploaded multiple images for my product but its only displaying the thumbnail&#8221; &#8220;I Activated Gold Cart but it has no settings?&#8221; &#8220;How can I make my grid view products the same height and [...]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Mychelle";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5189:"<ul>\n<li><em><strong>&#8220;I have activated my Gold Cart but grid view doesn&#8217;t work it still tells me to purchase the Gold Cart?&#8221;</strong></em></li>\n<li><em><strong>&#8220;I have uploaded multiple images for my product but its only displaying the thumbnail&#8221;</strong></em></li>\n<li><em><strong>&#8220;I Activated Gold Cart but it has no settings?&#8221;</strong></em></li>\n<li><strong><em>&#8220;How can I make my grid view products the same height and width?&#8221;</em></strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Sound familiar? These are the most commonly asked Gold Cart related questions in the Premium Support forum- and often the simplest to answer.  We took some time to remind you about these settings and solutions.  As a reminder, although the <a title="link to WP e-Commerce plugin" href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-e-commerce/">WP e-Commerce plugin will always be free in the WordPress repository</a>, the biggest benefit of <a title="WP e-Commerce Gold Cart" href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-plugin/gold-cart-plugin/">Gold Cart</a> is our one to one <a title="Support" href="http://getshopped.org/resources/premium-support/">support</a>.</p>\n<h2>&#8220;I have activated my Gold Cart but grid view doesn&#8217;t work it still tells me to purchase the Gold Cart?&#8221;</h2>\n<p><img class="size-full wp-image-270104 alignleft" style="margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" title="WP e-Commerce Plugin Purchase options" src="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Screen-shot-2012-05-28-at-9.51.12-AM.png" alt="" width="525" height="196" /><br />\nThe first thing to check here is your API Key. With the Gold Cart plugin you must install and activate the Gold Cart like any WordPress plugin, you must also activate the API Key that was included in your GetShopped purchase receipt.<br />\nTo quickly check if your key is activated (or to activate it) you can visit the store upgrades menu located under the main WordPress Dashboard.<br />\n<strong>Need more info? <a href="http://docs.getshopped.org/documentation/activating-your-gold-cart/">Visit the documentation!</a></strong></p>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div><img class=" wp-image-270105 alignleft" style="margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" title="WP e-Commerce plugin thumbnail setting" src="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Screen-shot-2012-05-28-at-9.54.03-AM.png" alt="" width="472" height="236" /></div>\n<h2>&#8220;I have uploaded multiple images for my product but its only displaying the thumbnail?&#8221;</h2>\n<p>&#8220;I Activated Gold Cart but it has no settings?&#8221;So you spent hours uploading images for all your products only to discover that your product page is still only displaying the main product thumbnail image?<br />\nIf you have this problem the first thing you should do is check your presentation settings page located under <em>settings &gt; store &gt;presentation</em>. In the thumbnails section is an option called show gallery or Show Thumbnail Gallery for some of you, this must be turned to yes if you would like your thumbnails to show.</p>\n<p>If your a early supporter of the Gold Cart and think your running an old version you may need to upgrade to make multiple images work with the 3.8 installs of WP e-Commerce. <a href="http://getshopped.org/extend/premium-upgrades-files/">You can upgrade your Gold Cart here</a></p>\n<p>This is another popular question which I think mainly comes from people conditioned to every plugin having its own menu. The current version of Gold Cart (2.9.7) does not have its own menu. Once activated correctly (API Key and plugin activation) the Gold Cart will simply extend on the options already in WP e-Commerce. Most of these settings can be found on the presentation settings page. If you&#8217;re unsure if your Gold Cart is activated the best way to tell is to look at your gateway list, WP e-Commerce should now have ALOT more gateways available for you to use.</p>\n<h2>How can I make my grid view products the same height and width?</h2>\n<p>Gold Cart by default works out the width for each grid item (based on how many across you set) and the height (depending on the length of the title and descriptions). Because each product grid can be a different height some product pages take on a staggered effect. You can get rid of this with some simple CSS.<br />\nYou will want to put this css into your child themes style.css or into your wpsc-default.css sheet if you have moved it into your theme folder.</p>\n<pre class="brush: php; title: ; notranslate">\r\n.product_grid_display .product_grid_item {\r\n   width:150px !important;\r\n   height: 200px !important;\r\n}\r\n</pre>\n<p>You will need to adjust the height and width to fit your design however keep in mind that this will be the width and height for all the grid view boxes from now on so make sure you choose a size that will fit with every product you have.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ll continue to answer some of our most popular questions about Gold Cart in the coming weeks. If you need help in the meanwhile, log into Premium Support and ask us for personalized help! Our support team is here to help.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/common-gold-cart-questions-answered/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"20";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:44:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:""