(185, 1, '2012-07-13 21:08:49', '2012-07-13 21:08:49', '<iframe	src			=	"http://masschallenge.org"\r\n			scrolling	=	"no"\r\n>	</iframe>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSmallTech supports an on site, full time developer in maintaining MassChallenge.org. This site is built on Drupal, and is their primary mechanism for delivering news, and services to their competition participants.\r\n<br/>	<br/>\r\n\r\nSite administration for MassChallenge means doing absolutely any thing, and every thing. The assigned task could be as simple as a content migration, and publishing to some thing as complex as deploying a reservation management system. Typically this involves a mix of using both the Drupal UI, and raw PHP / MySQL scripting in template files, and modules. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div id = ''secondsidebar'' >\r\n<ul	class	=	''project_summary''	>\r\n	<li>	<a	href	=	''http://masschallenge.org''	>	<h2>\r\n		MassChallenge\r\n	</h2>	</a>	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span	class	=	''type''	>	Industry:	</span>\r\n		<span	class	=	''data''	>	nonprofit	</span>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span	class	=	''type''	>	Location:	</span>\r\n		<span	class	=	''data''	>	Boston MA	</span>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span	class	=	''type''	>	Size:			</span>\r\n		<span	class	=	''data''	>	1 - 10 employees	</span>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span	class	=	''type''	>	Technology:	</span>\r\n		<span	class	=	''data''	>	Drupal	<br/>\r\n											git		<br/>\r\n											Acquia	<br/>\r\n											Sass		<br/>\r\n											JQuery\r\n		</span>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<span	class	=	''type''	>	Project:		</span>\r\n		<span	class	=	''data''	>	site administration	</span>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Mass Challenge', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '60-revision-16', '', '', '2012-07-13 21:08:49', '2012-07-13 21:08:49', '', 60, 'http://smalls.cc/2012/07/13/60-revision-16/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(186, 1, '2012-07-20 16:02:17', '2012-07-20 16:02:17', 'Social media can be a powerful tool in generating attention for your brand, but it can also be a huge distraction. The impulse to continously stream new content through social media outlets can be very tempting when we see statistics of how successful others may have been at it, but we also need to be wary of\r\n<a	href	=	''http://blog.limitedrun.com/post/28341629174/why-were-deleting-our-facebook-page''	>\r\n	the associated\r\n</a>\r\n<a href = ''http://techcrunch.com/2012/07/30/startup-claims-80-of-its-facebook-ad-clicks-are-coming-from-bots/'' > advertising costs,\r\n</a>\r\nand the different needs of every business.\r\n<br/>	<br/>\r\n\r\nOne of the easiest traps to fall into with social media is pushing content onto their sites without consideration of when, or how we might see a concrete benefit. Experience has shown that users go to social media sites to read news about their friends, and connections. Where we are able to insert our selves into their feeds, the typical result is that the readers will momentarily read our post, identify it as marketing, and gloss over it. At that point we have used our content to enrich the owners of the social media site without necessarily deriving any benefit for our selves, and this is contrary to our goal of calling them to action, and leveraging the \r\n<a	href	=	''http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Online_social_networks#Market_share''	>\r\n	massive audiences in social media sites \r\n</a>\r\ninto customers for our enterprises.\r\n<br/>	<br/>\r\n\r\nThe trick is to be just as strategic about social media as we are about the other elements of our marketing. That means a number of things:\r\n\r\n<ul class = ''post''>\r\n	<li>\r\n		being selective about what networks we use to target our intended audience, and recognizing what frame of mind their users are in. For instance Facebook, and Twitter users may be most interested in short, amusing content, or direct communication with their friends while CraigsList users are much more active shoppers, and sellers.\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		using our excellent content to draw traffic away from the social media sites, and into our businesses. The best, most active social media campaign is useless, if readers simply gloss over it, and continue to read different content on the same site. We want to initiate an action that directly benefits your business, whether that be a page view, a sale, or a referral, or a lead.\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'Social Media', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'social-media', '', '', '2012-08-01 13:56:17', '2012-08-01 13:56:17', '', 0, 'http://smalls.cc/?p=186', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(187, 1, '2012-07-20 16:01:55', '2012-07-20 16:01:55', 'Social media can be a powerful tool in generating attention for your brand, but it can also be a huge distraction. The impulse to continously stream new content through social media outlets can be very tempting when we see statistics of how successful others may have been at it, but every business is different.\n<br/>	<br/>\n\nOne of the easiest traps to fall into with social media is pushing content onto their sites without consideration of when, or how we might see a concrete benefit. Experience has shown that users go to social media sites to read news about their friends, and connections. Where we are able to insert our selves into their feeds, the typical result is that the readers will momentarily read our post, identify it as marketing, and gloss over it. This is contrary to our goal of calling them to action, and leveraging the massive audiences in social media sites into customers for our enterprises.\n<br/>	<br/>\n\nThe trick is to be just as strategic about social media as we are about the other elements of our marketing. That means being selective about what networks we use to target our intended audience, and recognizing what frame of mind their users are in, and how we can take advantage of that. That also means using our excellent content to draw traffic away from the social media sites, and into our businesses.', 'Social Media', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '186-revision', '', '', '2012-07-20 16:01:55', '2012-07-20 16:01:55', '', 186, 'http://smalls.cc/2012/07/20/186-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
